  "citation_spans": [
    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "A number of placebo-controlled clinical trials have shown that fesoterodine, imidafenacin, propiverine, solifenacin, and tolterodine were statistically significantly more effective at reducing the mean number of urgency episodes/24 h compared with placebo ( Figure 6 ). Pooled differences in mean changes from baseline varied between 0.4 and 1.7 episodes per day compared with placebo."
